
<h1>Patterns</h1>

<p>A pattern represents an ordered series of {{ doc('expr_intro', 'Expressions') }} that evaluate into notes or chords when used inside a {{ doc('clip') }}.</p>

<p>
<ul>
<li>Patterns include strings like:
<ul>
<li>"1"</li>
<li>"IV"</li>
<li>"C4sus4"</li>
<li>or even "C4sus4;O+1;cc0=50".</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Patterns can include velocity and MIDI CC information (see {{ doc('expr_mod') }}.
<li>A pattern may define an octave_shift to be applied to the current {{ doc('scale') }}, which applies <i>after</i> the base octave of the instrument.
<li>A pattern may define a Tempo to override the tempo of the {{ doc('scene') }} or {{ doc('song') }}, if not overriden by the {{ doc('clip') }}.
<li>A pattern may define a Scale to override the scale of the {{ doc('scene') }} or {{ doc('song') }}, if not overriden by a {{ doc('clip') }}.
</ul>
</p>

